PROJECT REPORT
Fake News Detection System (AI & ML Project)
1. Introduction
Fake news has become a major problem in the digital world due to the rapid spread of information on social media and news platforms. This project aims to build an AI-based system that can automatically classify news as real or fake using Machine Learning techniques.
2. Objective
To detect fake news using machine learning algorithms
To analyze text data from news articles
To build a web application for user interaction
To improve accuracy of classification using NLP techniques
3. Tools & Technologies Used
Python
Pandas
Scikit-learn
NLP (Natural Language Processing)
Flask (for web app)
HTML, CSS (Frontend)
Jupyter Notebook / VS Code
4. Dataset Description
The dataset used in this project contains two files:
Fake.csv → Fake news articles
True.csv → Real news articles
These datasets are combined into:
fake_news.csv
Each record contains:
Title
Text
Subject
Label (Fake / Real)
5. System Architecture
Data Collection (Fake.csv, True.csv)
Data Preprocessing (cleaning text, removing stopwords)
Feature Extraction (TF-IDF Vectorizer)
Model Training (Logistic Regression / Naive Bayes)
Model Saving (model.pkl, vectorizer.pkl)
Web Application (Flask app.py)
User Input Prediction
6. Project Structure Explanation
app.py → Flask backend for web application
train_model.py → Model training script
create_dataset.py → Combines Fake & True datasets
visualization.py ⭐ → Shows graphs (pie chart, distribution)
fake_news.csv → Final dataset
model.pkl → Saved ML model
vectorizer.pkl → TF-IDF vectorizer
templates/index.html → UI page
static/style.css → Styling
7. Methodology
Step 1: Data Preprocessing
Removing punctuation
Converting text to lowercase
Removing stopwords
Step 2: Feature Extraction
TF-IDF Vectorization is used to convert text into numerical form
Step 3: Model Training
Machine Learning model is trained on labeled dataset
Step 4: Prediction
User enters news text
Model predicts whether news is Fake or Real
8. Visualization 
The visualization.py file generates graphs such as:
Distribution of Fake vs Real news
Pie chart representation of dataset balance
9. Results
The model successfully classifies news articles
High accuracy achieved using NLP techniques
Web interface allows easy user interaction
10. Conclusion
The Fake News Detection System helps identify misinformation using Machine Learning. It provides a simple and interactive way for users to verify news authenticity.
11. Future Improvements
Use Deep Learning (LSTM / BERT)
Improve accuracy with larger datasets
Add real-time news scraping
Deploy on cloud (Heroku / AWS)